<Base
  title="Attribution | Resting Places"
  description="Source attribution for the open data behind Resting Places: Wikidata, Wikimedia Commons, OpenStreetMap, and Wikipedia."
>
  <h1>Attribution</h1>
  <p class="lede">Resting Places is built from open data. This page credits every source and states how each is used.</p>

  <h2>Wikidata</h2>
  <p>
    Structured facts (names, locations, coordinates, founding dates, area, heritage status, official websites, notable
    interments, and external identifiers) come from <a href="https://www.wikidata.org/">Wikidata</a>, published under the
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/">CC0 1.0 public domain dedication</a>. Every cemetery page
    links its source item.
  </p>

  <h2>Wikimedia Commons</h2>
  <p>
    Photographs come from <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/">Wikimedia Commons</a>. Each image's license is verified
    through the Commons API before display, each image carries an inline credit and license link where it appears, and the
    complete inventory is on the <a href="/image-credits/">image credits</a> page.
  </p>

  <h2>OpenStreetMap</h2>
  <p>
    Fallback coordinates for a small number of entries come from OpenStreetMap's Nominatim geocoder.
    Map data © <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OpenStreetMap contributors</a>, available under the
    Open Database License. Pages using these coordinates say so in their facts table. Where a page's "Opening hours"
    section is credited to OpenStreetMap, that value is a real <code>opening_hours</code> tag on a matching OSM feature,
    queried live through the public <a href="https://overpass-api.de/">Overpass API</a> and shown verbatim, not
    reformatted.
  </p>

  <h2>Wikipedia</h2>
  <p>
    We link to Wikipedia articles for narrative history. We do not reproduce Wikipedia's text, which is licensed
    CC BY-SA; descriptions on this site are original and derived from the structured facts above.
  </p>

  <h2>Google Places</h2>
  <p>
    Where a page's "Opening hours" section is credited to Google Places, that value was fetched live through the
    Google Places API (Text Search to resolve the listing, then Place Details for the hours themselves) and is
    shown with the date it was checked. Hours are only ever shown when a live source actually returned one; most
    cemeteries carry no formal published hours at all and correctly show no "Opening hours" section rather than a
    guess.
  </p>

  <h2>Find a Grave and BillionGraves</h2>
  <p>
    Some pages link to Find a Grave as an external reference. We do not ingest, scrape, or republish content or photographs
    from Find a Grave, BillionGraves, or any genealogy service; the link identifier itself comes from Wikidata's CC0 records.
  </p>
</Base>
